<h2>Seven Readings — Seven Darśanas</h2>
<p>The same 88 characters. Each reading produces different <em>words</em> — different doctrinal claims — not just different numbers of the same words.</p>

<div class="reading-box">
<div class="reading-title">9 Names — The Traditional Maximum</div>
<div class="reading-desc">BORI / Śaṅkara. Uses 8 of 55 split points. The MOST CONSERVATIVE reading — every compound held together as one name. 0.4% of all grammatically valid decompositions.</div>
